253
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:05,033
But the thing is,
Okoy did a lousy job.

254
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:07,067
Why?

255
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:11,200
Cecilia told me that the police
still suspect

256
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:12,600
that the person
who killed Donabel

257
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:14,200
was someone inside the beauty
pageant.

258
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:18,500
Tell Okoy about that, okay?

259
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:20,367
He knows what he's going to do.

260
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:33,333
Here are our ten official
candidates

261
00:15:33,467 --> 00:15:35,967
of Miss Calabari 2025.

262
00:15:36,133 --> 00:15:37,300
Are you ready, girls?

263
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:42,700
All right, let's start
with Charlie Samson.

264
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,200
See?

265
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:50,333
First pick.

266
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:57,300
And our second contestant is...

267
00:15:57,433 --> 00:15:59,133
Teresa Legazpi.

268
00:16:09,667 --> 00:16:14,533
Now, for our 5th finalist,
we have Miss Peach Mongolia.

269
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:22,967
And our 9th contestant is...

270
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,600
Apple Castro!

271
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:31,867
And now,

272
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,933
for our last candidate
to complete

273
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:38,633
the Miss Calabari 2025 list
is...

274
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:43,167
Bobby Enriquez!

275
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:03,833
Hey, go there.

276
00:17:03,967 --> 00:17:05,333
The first pick should be here,
right?

277
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,733
It's just the same.

278
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:09,800
Congratulations!

279
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:15,333
All right, so here's our
complete 10 official finalists

280
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,700
of Miss Calabari 2025!

281
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:35,767
Boss...

282
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:38,900
the official list and file

283
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:42,367
of the 20th Calabari Beauty
pageant is here.

284
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,433
In fairness,
they are all very beautiful.

285
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:48,467
And Okoy has also sent a copy
of this to our clients.

286
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:50,267
They can now go window shopping.

287
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,500
Good.

288
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:00,067
Since you're already
window shopping...

289
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:03,200
take a look at the two
at the end,

290
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:05,467
especially the last one.

291
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,000
You know her very well.

292
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:23,300
Let me warn you, Boss.
Those women are all beautiful.

293
00:18:23,467 --> 00:18:27,667
Our clients will choose them.
And if that happens, we're done.

294
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,033
Those are police officials.

295
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,567
That's not my concern.

296
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:36,300
Why would two police officials
want to join a beauty pageant?

297
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:39,200
And as far as I know,

298
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:42,433
Bobby's not the type to want
to be a beauty queen.

299
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:49,900
They have other agendas.

300
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,900
Let's just ride along with them.

301
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:20,167
Bobby!

302
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:22,167
Sir...

303
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:23,100
How are you?

304
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:27,933
Well, Lieutenant Samson
and I got in.

305
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,400
Very good.

306
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:32,033
The truth is,
I'm not really surprised.

307
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,600
By the way, I brought you
a snack.

308
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:37,900
Maybe you'd like
some cinnamon rolls.

309
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:39,300
Cinnamon roll?

310
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:42,200
Sorry, I don't eat that.

311
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:44,567
Actually, that's my least
favorite bread.

312
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:45,667
Is that so?

313
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:46,600
You can have it.

314
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,600
Oh my, sorry, I didn't know.

315
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:50,000
That's a shame.

316
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,767
Tonyo!

317
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,067
Samson!

318
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:57,533
Good thing you two
got in the pageant.

319
00:19:58,633 --> 00:20:00,200
It'll be easier for you
to keep an eye

320
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:02,067
on what's going on inside.

321
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:03,167
Actually,

322
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:06,133
I haven't noticed anything
suspicious inside.

323
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:08,600
Me too, Sir, I haven't noticed
anything yet.

324
00:20:08,733 --> 00:20:10,100
What makes you say that?

325
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:13,733
Aren't you busy flirting with
the sponsor at the comfort room?

326
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:17,333
Wait, wait...

327
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:20,300
Flirting at the comfort room?

328
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,800
Men's comfort room.

329
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:23,733
Bobby, tell him!

330
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,833
I don't have to explain
anything, Sir!

331
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:31,067
Bobby Enriquez, right?

332
00:20:32,667 --> 00:20:33,900
Sir Jared.

333
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:36,933
Congratulations!
You're a finalist.

334
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:39,933
But, Sir, she was called last,
right?

335
00:20:40,067 --> 00:20:42,933
It seems like the judges
were forced to do it

336
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:44,600
because they feel sorry for her.

337
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:50,433
Did you know that in a contest,
when you're called last,

338
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:52,500
usually, you're the strongest.

339
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:55,800
Those who were called first
are the weak ones.

340
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:01,600
Bobby, by the way...

341
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:03,800
remember what we talked about
earlier in the comfort room,

342
00:21:03,933 --> 00:21:05,767
that will push through, okay?
Let's have coffee.

343
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:06,667
No, you can't.

344
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,100
What's that, Bro?

345
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:15,533
What's that, Bro?

346
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:21,633
Me, I can't come later
because I have something to do.

347
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:26,400
That's okay, Sir. He's not
asking you, he's asking me.

348
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:29,433
Maybe you'll invite me.

349
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:30,833
I'll be busy later.

350
00:21:32,233 --> 00:21:33,133
Okay.

351
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:34,300
So, Bobby...

352
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:36,000
there's a nice cafe here.

353
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:37,000
I'll see you?

354
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:38,067
Okay, Sir.

355
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,833
I'll just say goodbye
to my friends.

356
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:41,867
All right.

357
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:43,267
Congrats again.

358
00:21:50,233 --> 00:21:51,300
Excuse me.

359
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:04,200
That's Jared Lopez,
CEO of Add2Cart.

360
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,700
He's the major sponsor
of Miss Calabari,

361
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:09,167
and he's the one Bobby
was talking to

362
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,867
in the men's comfort room.

363
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,233
So what if he's big-time?

364
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:18,433
He looks so pale, like he
doesn't get enough sunlight.

365
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:19,833
Don't get jealous.

366
00:22:19,967 --> 00:22:21,233
You and Bobby are not together,
right?

367
00:22:21,367 --> 00:22:23,400
I'm not jealous.
That's not my style.

368
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,600
I came here for work.

369
00:22:25,733 --> 00:22:27,067
Whatever you say.

370
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:30,467
Well, if you want to make Bobby
jealous, I'm game.

371
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,800
Just tell me.

372
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:36,467
What if you go back to
the precinct with me?

373
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,800
- Oh, no.
- Let's go.

374
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:39,433
No.

375
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,833
You can go ahead.
I need to go somewhere else.

376
00:22:41,967 --> 00:22:43,633
- Okay.
- Here.

377
00:22:43,767 --> 00:22:45,500
Do you want some cinnamon rolls?

378
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:48,100
How did you know that
this was my favorite?

379
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,000
Tonyo, you're so sweet.

380
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:53,300
- Thank you. Take care.
- Okay.

381
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,167
I heard that the coffee here
is really good,

382
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,167
especially when you have it
with a cinnamon roll.

383
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:20,700
You know, cinnamon roll
is my favorite.

384
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:22,567
That's really good,
especially with coffee, right?

385
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:23,500
Right?

386
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,100
Lieutenant Conde?

387
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,333
Bobby?

388
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:31,367
I just found out that Bobby
is joining Miss Calabari.

389
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:35,467
Aren't you one of the judges
of Miss Calabari?

390
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,667
You already know what to do.

391
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,100
I'll just do a background check
on someone Bobby knows.

392
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:40,633
Jared Lopez.

393
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:43,233
He's the CEO of Add2Cart.

394
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,300
I called the company,

395
00:23:44,433 --> 00:23:47,100
but I was told that the CEO
is someone else,

396
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,833
not Jared Lopez.
